In this speech, President Trump addresses a gathering to commemorate American peace officers who have died in the line of duty. He expresses gratitude for their sacrifice and praises law enforcement as heroes. The President also condemns anti-police rhetoric and calls for stricter punishment for criminals who pose a threat to public safety. He highlights the case of Corporal Ronil Singh, an officer who was killed by an undocumented immigrant, and emphasizes the need for stronger border security. The President concludes by thanking the families of fallen officers and pledging unwavering support for law enforcement.